<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Curvt2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Curvét,</orth> vb. to leap, to bound: <cit><quote>he rears upright, --s and leaps,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 279" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 279</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>cry holla to thy tongue, it --s unseasonably,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.258" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 258</bibl></cit>.
